==Korean==
===Noun===
'''물개''' (''mulgae'') (''literally, "[[water]] [[dog]]"'')
# [[ear]]ed [[seal]], [[fur]] [[seal]], [[sea lion]] 
# [[otter]]

====Synonyms====
*[[바다사자]] (''bada-saja'') [[sea lion]] (eared), literally, "[[sea]] [[lion]]"
*[[해구]] ([[海狗]], ''haegu'') [[fur]] [[seal]] (eared), literally, "[[sea]] [[dog]]" cf. German [[Seehund]] (as if a literal translation)
*[[수달]] ([[水獺]], ''sudal'') [[otter]], literally, "[[water]] [[otter]]" (Both English words are cognate, hence a tautologic Sino-Korean as usual.) 

